article.headline: Winthrop 74, VMI 69
article.story: LEXINGTON , Va. (AP) -- Torrell Martin scored 19 of his 26 points in the second half Monday night when Winthrop broke open a close game and held on to beat VMI 74-69. The Eagles (14-5, 8-1 Big South) used a 9-0 run to begin the second half to pull away from a 31-all halftime tie, built it as high as 13 and never let VMI closer than three. Reggie Williams had 21 points and Matt Murrer had 15 points and 15 rebounds for the Keydets (7-12, 2-6), but VMI could not overcome 25 turnovers. Craig Bradshaw added 15 points for Winthrop, including a pair of free throws with four seconds left after VMI closed to 72-69. The Eagles scored 24 points off turnovers.
